                                +"initial-scale=1.0,"
                                +"maximum-scale=1.0,"
                                +"user-scalable=no")

    link(rel="stylesheet" href="./index.css")
  body
    .reveal
      .slides
        section#start
          h1 Introduction to Solid
          p By Arne Hassel
        section#agenda
          h2 Agenda
        section#about-me
          h2 About me
          ul
            li.fragment Senior front-end developer at&nbsp;
              a(href="https://inrupt.com/") Inrupt
              |  since 2018
            li.fragment Contributing to&nbsp;
              a(href="https://solidproject.org/") Solid
              |   since 2018
            li.fragment Interested in&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/standards/semanticweb/data") Linked Data
              |  since 2011
        section#solid-10000-ft
          h2 Solid from 10.000 ft
          blockquote
            | Solid is a&nbsp;
            a(href="https://solidproject.org/TR/") specification
            |  that lets people store their data securely in decentralized data stores called Pods.
            | Pods are like secure personal web servers for data. When data is stored in someone's Pod,
            | they control which people and applications can access it.
          p From&nbsp;
            a(href="https://solidproject.org/") solidproject.org
          ul
            li.fragment Started by&nbsp;
              a(href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tim_Berners-Lee") Tim Berners-Lee
            li.fragment Origin: Social Linked Data - SoLiD (not used anymore)
        section#solid-org
          h2 Organization
          ul
            li.fragment No single organization
            li.fragment Panels (e.g.&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/community/solid/wiki/Authentication_Panel") authentication
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/community/solid/wiki/Authorization_Panel") authorization
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/community/solid/wiki/Interoperability_Panel") interoperability
              | )
            li.fragment Other&nbsp;
              a(href="https://solidproject.org/contributing") volunteers
            li.fragment Developers and organizations
            li.fragment Other interested parties (via social channels)
        section#solid-not
          h2 What Solid is <u>not</u>
          ul
            li.fragment Blockchain
            li.fragment SOLID principles
            li.fragment solid.js
        section#linked-data-basics
          h2 Linked Data basics
          ul
            li.fragment RDF (
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf11-concepts/") Specification
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf-primer/") Primer
              | )
            li.fragment Triples
              img(src="./assets/rdf-graph.svg", style="margin: 0 1em;")
            li.fragment Graphs (e.g.&nbsp;
              a(href="https://id.inrupt.com/megoth") https://id.inrupt.com/megoth
              | )
            li.fragment Serializations (e.g.&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/turtle/") Turtle
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://json-ld.org/") JSON-LD
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf-syntax-grammar/") RDF/XML
              | )
            li.fragment Vocabularies/Ontologies (e.g.&nbsp;
              a(href="https://schema.org/") schema.org
              | )
            li.fragment Queries (i.e.&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf-sparql-query/") SPARQL
              | )
            li.fragment Shapes (
              a(href="http://shex.io/") ShEx
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.w3.org/TR/shacl/") SHACL
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://shaperepo.com/") ShapeRepo
              | )
        section#solid-implementations
          h2 Solid implementations
          ul
            li.fragment Server implementations (
              a(href="https://inrupt.com/products/enterprise-solid-server/") ESS
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://github.com/CommunitySolidServer/CommunitySolidServer") CSS
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://github.com/nodeSolidServer/node-solid-server") NSS
              | )
            li.fragment Client-side implementations (
              a(href="https://docs.inrupt.com/developer-tools/javascript/client-libraries/") Inrupt
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://github.com/linkeddata/rdflib.js/") rdflib.js
              | ,&nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/ldo") LDO
              | )
            li.fragment
              a(href="https://solidproject.org/developers/tools/") List of tools
        section#pros-cons-developers
          h2 Pros & Cons - Developers
          ul(style="list-style: none;")
            li.fragment + Reusable and extensible data
            li.fragment + GDPR-compliant
            li.fragment + Good combo w/headless apps
            li.fragment - Complicated
            li.fragment - Specifications under development
            li.fragment - No significant network effect (yet)
        section#pros-cons-users
          h2 Pros & Cons - Users
          ul(style="list-style: none;")
            li.fragment + No lock-in
            li.fragment + Reusable data
            li.fragment + Allows full control of data
            li.fragment - Few apps
            li.fragment - Challenging UX
        section#links
          h2 More links
          ul
            li.fragment
              a(href="https://forum.solidproject.org/") Forum
            li.fragment
              a(href="https://gitter.im/solid/chat") Gitter chat
            li.fragment
              a(href="https://solidproject.org/events") Solid World
            li.fragment
              a(href="https://solidproject.org/apps") Apps
              ul
                li.fragment
                  a(href="https://podbrowser.inrupt.com") Inrupt PodBrowser
                li.fragment
                  a(href="https://penny.vincenttunru.com/") Penny
                li.fragment
                  a(href="https://noeldemartin.github.io/media-kraken/") Media Kraken
                li.fragment
                  a(href="https://liqid.chat/") Liqid Chat
                li.fragment
                  a(href="https://formgenerator.smessie.com/") Form Generator
        section#thank-you
          h2 Questions?
          p Thank you ^_^
